 boats backMajority of asylum seekers in Ireland are POURING in from the UKMore than 400 migrants crossed the Channel on same day five others drowned in French watersFrench police officers patrolling the beach between Ambleteusse and Wimereux|GETTY\\\"We need men, we need arms\\\", the mayor insisted.He added: \\\"If there had been a sufficient police presence, this tragedy would not have happened.\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1884, \"end\": 1896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Anderson_(British_politician)\", \"score\": 0.9282608898945314, \"rank\": 0.05681818181818276, \"text\": \"Lee Anderson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Anderson_(British_politician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Anderson_(British_politician)\"}, {\"begin\": 1987, \"end\": 1994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9933982491232548, \"rank\": 0.006645568317864054, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 2099, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5417147916687172, \"rank\": 0.5207724254327039, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jean-Luc Duba\\u00e9le\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1793}, {\"ngram\": \"a desperate need\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1825}, {\"ngram\": \"more policing resources\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1853}, {\"ngram\": \"government\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1913}, {\"ngram\": \"boats\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"backMajority\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1965}, {\"ngram\": \"asylum seekers\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1983}, {\"ngram\": \"the UKMore\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"than 400 migrants\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2043}, {\"ngram\": \"the Channel\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2063}, {\"ngram\": \"same day\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2075}, {\"ngram\": \"five others\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2087}, {\"ngram\": \"the beach\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2155}, {\"ngram\": \"Ambleteusse\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2175}, {\"ngram\": \"Wimereux|GETTY\\\"We\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2197}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2206}, {\"ngram\": \"arms\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2220}, {\"ngram\": \"the mayor\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"a sufficient police presence\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2299}, {\"ngram\": \"this tragedy\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Officials around Wimereux, which is just north of Boulogne have complained for some time that far too few police officers are being stationed along what if one of the busiest stretches of coastline for migrant boat launches.Fr\\u00e9d\\u00e9ric Okonek said the increasing level of migrant violence was posing a huge problem for police in the area near Boulogne, who he said had a fraction of the resources of areas like Calais.Huge numbers of migrants are still coming to Britain via small boats |PA\\\"In Boulogne we have a big problem with the number of migrants.\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2356, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wimereux\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wimereux\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wimereux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wimereux\"}, {\"begin\": 2389, \"end\": 2397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boulogne-sur-Mer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.258456421564823e-15, \"text\": \"Boulogne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boulogne-sur-Mer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boulogne-sur-Mer\"}, {\